# Anti-996 License

Version 1.0, March 2019

Copyright (C) 2019 Jian Weihao

## PREAMBLE

The purpose of this License is to prevent the adoption of 996 work schedules (9:00-21:00, 6 days per week) in software companies and organizations. We believe that long working hours are harmful to employees' health and well-being, and unsustainable for businesses in the long run.

## TERMS AND CONDITIONS

### 0. Definitions

"This License" refers to Anti-996 License Version 1.0.

"Copyright" also means copyright-like laws that apply to other kinds of works, such as semiconductor masks.

"The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this License.

### 1. Grant of Copyright License

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, Jian Weihao hereby grants you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual (for the duration of the applicable copyright) license to exercise the rights in the Program as stated below:

a) You may reproduce and distribute copies of the Program or derivative works thereof in any medium, with or without modifications, and in Source or Object form, provided that you meet the following conditions:

   i) You must cause any modified files to carry prominent notices stating that you changed the files.

   ii) You must retain, in the Source form of any derivative works that you distribute, all copyright, patent, trademark, and attribution notices from the Source form of the Program, excluding those notices that do not pertain to any part of the derivative works.

   iii) You must include this license file or notice in every copy or substantial portion of the derivative works.

### 2. Anti-996 Provision

a) Any company, organization, or individual (collectively "Licensee") that uses, copies, modifies, publishes, or distributes the Program or any derivative work thereof ("Using the Software") MUST NOT implement or enforce a 996 work schedule (9:00 AM to 9:00 PM, 6 days per week) for any of its employees, contractors, or agents.

b) "Implementing or enforcing a 996 work schedule" includes, but is not limited to:

   - Having regular work hours that extend beyond 9:00 PM
   - Having regular work days that extend beyond 5 days per week
   - Having on-call or overtime that results in effective 996 working conditions
   - Requiring employees to be available during non-working hours on a regular basis

c) If a Licensee is found to be implementing or enforcing a 996 work schedule, the license granted under this License to that Licensee is automatically terminated as of the date such practice is discovered.

### 3. Termination for Cause

This License and the rights granted hereunder will terminate automatically if you fail to comply with any term of this License. Upon termination, you must immediately cease all use of the Program and destroy all copies, in whole or in part.

